The heavy water tank can be used as a thermal

The thermal neutron flux at the sample irradiation
measurement, the samples of Dy, Hf and Au were put on
an aluminium sample holder. The irradiation time was
3-hr during the 5-MW operation of the Kyoto University
For the resonance integrals measurements, the samples
Dy and Hf were put into a Cd-cover 0.5-mm in thickness
and attached on an aluminium sample holder. A set of
Dy and Au or Hf and Au was irradiated during 2-3hr
with a nominal power of 1 Wt.
The neutron fluxes during the irradiation were measured
on Au foil (12.7mm in diameter, 50 mm in thickness).
The neutron intensities among the irradiation runs
were monitored by a pair of Au foils (10mm in diameter
and 20 mm in thickness) which were set at the upper
and lower positions 7.5 cm from the center.
